President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the deployment and redeployment of permanent secretaries. Folasade Yemi-Esan, Head of the Civil Service of the Federation (HOCSF), made this known in a circular on Friday. Chinyeaka Christian has been redeployed from Ministry of Federal Capital Territory (FCT) to Ministry of Power; William Alo from Ministry of Labour and Employment to Ministry of Special Duties and Intergovernmental Affairs; Olusade Adesola from Ministry of Niger Delta Affairs to FCT; Esther Jack from Ministry of Power to Ministry of Water Resources. Akpan Sunday from Ministry of Mines and Steel Development to Ministry of Science and Technology; Ernest Afolabi from OHCSF to Ministry of Works and Housing; Abel Anitan from Federal Civil Service Commission to Ministry of Environment; Maurice Mbaeri from Ministry of Police Affairs to Office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (OSGF). Festus Daudu from Ministry of Special Duties and Intergovernmental Affairs to OHCSF; Magdalene Ajani from OHCSF to Ministry of Transport; Nebalisa Anako from Police Service Commission to Ministry of Information and Culture; Aliyu Ahmed moving from Ministry of Finance (Special Duties) to the same ministry; Temitope Fashedemi from OHCSF to Ministry of Police Affairs. In fresh deployments, Babangida Hussaini moves to Ministry of Defence; Yerima Peter to Ministry of Labour and Employment; Bayayo Kumo to Ministry of Niger Delta Affairs; Adaora Anyanwutaku to Ministry of Women Affairs; Anthonia Ekpa to Ministry of Foreign Affairs. Oluwatoyin Akinlade to Ministry of Mines and Steel Development; Aliyu Mohammed to OSGF; Emmanuel Meribola to OHCSF; Monilola Udoh to Federal Civil Service Commission; Mamman Mahmuda to OHCSF, Bashir Alkali to Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs; Shuaib Belgore to Ministry of Interior. The redeployment and deployment dates are between August 27 and September 30. Yemi-Esan directed that the handing and taking over processes be completed within the time frame.